On the 5th of September 2025, [Angela Rayner resigned](https://www.reuters.com/world/uk/uks-starmer-reshuffles-top-team-restore-authority-after-rayner-blow-2025-09-05/) as Deputy Prime Minister, Minister for housing, and Deputy leader of the UK Labour Party. This has triggered/will trigger a [deputy leadership election within the UK Labour Party](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2025_Labour_Party_deputy_leadership_election).&#x20;

[In order to stand in the election](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/angela-rayner-quit-labour-election-b2820932.html), a person must receive nominations from 20% of sitting labor MPs, over 5% of constituency labor parties, and at least three Labour Party affiliates (such as trade unions). Once candidates have secured these nominations, a ballot is held in which Labour members and affiliates can vote. The ballot is preferential, and voters will mark in order of preference.  More detail can be found in the [UK Labour Party Rule Book](https://labour.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Rule-Book-2024.pdf).

Ballots close on the 23rd of October according to [Sky](https://news.sky.com/story/labour-deputy-leadership-contest-how-does-it-work-and-who-is-eligible-to-vote-13427511). Results will be announced on the 25th. Potential candidates were sourced from [here](https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2025/sep/06/who-could-replace-angela-rayner-as-deputy-labour-leader), [here](https://news.williamhill.com/politics/next-labour-deputy-prime-minister-odds-following-angela-rayner-resignation/), and [here](https://www.thetimes.com/uk/politics/article/who-could-replace-angela-rayner-the-likely-candidates-pc7nf5bdh).&#x20;

[Updates on the election will be published here as they become available.](https://labour.org.uk/updates/members-updates/deputy-leadership-election-2025/)

